WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.435 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:02.435 --> 00:00:22.545 align:middle line:90%


00:00:22.545 --> 00:00:23.415 align:middle line:90%
>> Books love me.

00:00:23.415 --> 00:00:26.030 align:middle line:90%


00:00:26.030 --> 00:00:28.530 align:middle line:10%
>> The name of the library
is Bibliotheca Philosophica

00:00:28.530 --> 00:00:33.010 align:middle line:10%
Hermetica, the Library
of Hermetic Philosophy.

00:00:33.010 --> 00:00:35.840 align:middle line:84%
This library, with the
rare books and manuscripts,

00:00:35.840 --> 00:00:39.300 align:middle line:90%
altogether, some 23,000 volumes.

00:00:39.300 --> 00:00:43.820 align:middle line:84%
>> The possibilities that I
had to buy books was always

00:00:43.820 --> 00:00:50.120 align:middle line:84%
combined with the task to
produce every day a result

00:00:50.120 --> 00:00:51.410 align:middle line:90%
as an entrepreneur.

00:00:51.410 --> 00:00:54.520 align:middle line:90%
So I built a company.

00:00:54.520 --> 00:00:58.310 align:middle line:84%
And I made out of the
profits of my company.

00:00:58.310 --> 00:01:02.240 align:middle line:84%
But it is not so that the books
come like birds into the house

00:01:02.240 --> 00:01:04.489 align:middle line:90%
of treasures of Mr. Ritman.

00:01:04.489 --> 00:01:10.700 align:middle line:10%
Now, you have to make an
effort to acquire them.

00:01:10.700 --> 00:01:12.530 align:middle line:90%
I built a library.

00:01:12.530 --> 00:01:14.070 align:middle line:90%
I bought books.

00:01:14.070 --> 00:01:15.620 align:middle line:90%
I brought them together.

00:01:15.620 --> 00:01:20.060 align:middle line:10%
The books that are
on the shelves,

00:01:20.060 --> 00:01:24.800 align:middle line:10%
you have to open the
information suddenly.

00:01:24.800 --> 00:01:26.900 align:middle line:84%
You come to the point
that you are not

00:01:26.900 --> 00:01:30.776 align:middle line:90%
standing alone any longer.

00:01:30.776 --> 00:01:34.070 align:middle line:84%
And that is the
fantastic point what I

00:01:34.070 --> 00:01:37.550 align:middle line:90%
call, the chain of [INAUDIBLE].

00:01:37.550 --> 00:01:40.580 align:middle line:10%
We are invited to be members.

00:01:40.580 --> 00:01:42.980 align:middle line:84%
>> That's what I love
most in this library.

00:01:42.980 --> 00:01:47.660 align:middle line:84%
To see that in every single
book in a different way.

00:01:47.660 --> 00:01:50.960 align:middle line:90%
And a book doesn't stand alone.

00:01:50.960 --> 00:01:52.790 align:middle line:90%
They stand together.

00:01:52.790 --> 00:01:57.230 align:middle line:84%
They are like in a continuous
conversation with each other.

00:01:57.230 --> 00:01:59.930 align:middle line:90%
And that's what fascinates me.

00:01:59.930 --> 00:02:03.760 align:middle line:10%
>> By Western esotericism,
we mean a set of currents

00:02:03.760 --> 00:02:08.300 align:middle line:10%
of movements, of authors, that
can go back basically to Late

00:02:08.300 --> 00:02:11.990 align:middle line:10%
Antiquity and then to the
Middle Ages with a big revival

00:02:11.990 --> 00:02:14.480 align:middle line:10%
in the early modern period
during the Renaissance.

00:02:14.480 --> 00:02:17.860 align:middle line:84%
And then which continue
during the Enlightenment

00:02:17.860 --> 00:02:20.960 align:middle line:84%
and also throughout the
19th and 20th century.

00:02:20.960 --> 00:02:22.880 align:middle line:90%
Basically up to our days.

00:02:22.880 --> 00:02:30.770 align:middle line:84%
>> Western esotericism is
the study from the outside

00:02:30.770 --> 00:02:33.860 align:middle line:90%
to the inner reality.

00:02:33.860 --> 00:02:35.870 align:middle line:84%
You can call that
occult streams,

00:02:35.870 --> 00:02:38.430 align:middle line:84%
you can call that
esoteric streams.

00:02:38.430 --> 00:02:40.790 align:middle line:84%
You can call that
hermetic streams.

00:02:40.790 --> 00:02:45.560 align:middle line:84%
It is like to dive into
all the different aspects

00:02:45.560 --> 00:02:47.970 align:middle line:90%
of a tradition.

00:02:47.970 --> 00:02:52.110 align:middle line:84%
>> Traditions that emerged
and developed mostly in Europe

00:02:52.110 --> 00:02:54.330 align:middle line:90%
and in the Mediterranean basin.

00:02:54.330 --> 00:03:00.110 align:middle line:84%
>> To compose an alphabet
of understanding.

00:03:00.110 --> 00:03:04.820 align:middle line:84%
But it never gives the meaning
of the language itself.

00:03:04.820 --> 00:03:07.460 align:middle line:10%
>> Approaching the
divine, approaching kind

00:03:07.460 --> 00:03:12.740 align:middle line:10%
of metaphysical reality,
are precisely what we can

00:03:12.740 --> 00:03:16.160 align:middle line:10%
understand as the
core of esotericism.

00:03:16.160 --> 00:03:22.100 align:middle line:84%
>> I was very interested
in the human presence.

00:03:22.100 --> 00:03:28.870 align:middle line:84%
But not as the end of the story,
but the beginning of the story

00:03:28.870 --> 00:03:32.670 align:middle line:90%
where I said, what is the man?

00:03:32.670 --> 00:03:34.232 align:middle line:90%
Why is he here?

00:03:34.232 --> 00:03:40.310 align:middle line:84%
He comes from the invisible, he
lives here, and he disappears.

00:03:40.310 --> 00:03:43.580 align:middle line:84%
If you look through
the Hubble telescope

00:03:43.580 --> 00:03:45.600 align:middle line:84%
you can see this
infinite universe.

00:03:45.600 --> 00:03:52.020 align:middle line:84%
And you see all different forms
of energy that are, in a way,

00:03:52.020 --> 00:03:54.410 align:middle line:90%
on the move.

00:03:54.410 --> 00:03:59.510 align:middle line:84%
Perhaps we did not know but
we are experiencing a Big Bang

00:03:59.510 --> 00:04:01.130 align:middle line:90%
again.

00:04:01.130 --> 00:04:04.340 align:middle line:90%
We say you have the elements--

00:04:04.340 --> 00:04:08.020 align:middle line:90%
Earth, Water, Air, and Fire.

00:04:08.020 --> 00:04:13.460 align:middle line:84%
But I believe, for myself,
that there's a new element

00:04:13.460 --> 00:04:16.579 align:middle line:90%
in the atmosphere.

00:04:16.579 --> 00:04:23.560 align:middle line:84%
A new element in the atmosphere
that was invisible and came

00:04:23.560 --> 00:04:30.100 align:middle line:84%
to mystery schools and under the
protection of ceremonies where

00:04:30.100 --> 00:04:32.900 align:middle line:90%
there is a holy of holiness.

00:04:32.900 --> 00:04:39.340 align:middle line:84%
There this divine energy
was kept as a secret.

00:04:39.340 --> 00:04:42.350 align:middle line:84%
I think that divine
energy is now

00:04:42.350 --> 00:04:47.125 align:middle line:84%
available to billions
and millions of persons.

00:04:47.125 --> 00:04:50.070 align:middle line:84%
And that is the
so-called individualism.

00:04:50.070 --> 00:04:57.090 align:middle line:84%
Why if that doesn't refer any
longer, not a second longer,

00:04:57.090 --> 00:05:00.630 align:middle line:84%
with the old tradition,
with the old generation,

00:05:00.630 --> 00:05:04.130 align:middle line:84%
with the way you think,
you live, you are?

00:05:04.130 --> 00:05:08.760 align:middle line:10%
The domination of
the past is broken.

00:05:08.760 --> 00:05:10.065 align:middle line:90%
It all ends in anarchy.

00:05:10.065 --> 00:05:11.010 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:05:11.010 --> 00:05:13.780 align:middle line:90%
And that you see in this moment.

00:05:13.780 --> 00:05:19.110 align:middle line:84%
The international
power feuds, conflicts,

00:05:19.110 --> 00:05:21.720 align:middle line:90%
that we are in a crisis.

00:05:21.720 --> 00:05:26.020 align:middle line:84%
Nobody can say, I have
nothing to do with that.

00:05:26.020 --> 00:05:29.220 align:middle line:90%
It comes closer and closer.

00:05:29.220 --> 00:05:31.750 align:middle line:90%
We are not independent.

00:05:31.750 --> 00:05:37.980 align:middle line:84%
We are very dependent, more and
more dependent, to each other,

00:05:37.980 --> 00:05:40.400 align:middle line:90%
as we thought in the past.

00:05:40.400 --> 00:05:41.900 align:middle line:84%
>> We have main
collecting areas.

00:05:41.900 --> 00:05:46.110 align:middle line:10%
And they are Hermetica, Alchemy,
Mysticism and Rosicrucianism.

00:05:46.110 --> 00:05:50.390 align:middle line:84%
But related collecting areas
are Kabbalah but also theosophy,

00:05:50.390 --> 00:05:53.920 align:middle line:84%
anthroposophy, so the more
modern movements originating

00:05:53.920 --> 00:05:57.050 align:middle line:84%
from the 19th century
can also be found here.

00:05:57.050 --> 00:05:59.870 align:middle line:84%
>> Esotericism is in
fact a modern word.

00:05:59.870 --> 00:06:03.510 align:middle line:84%
Because it was created
in the 19th century.

00:06:03.510 --> 00:06:05.990 align:middle line:84%
But in fact, the history
of the term is older.

00:06:05.990 --> 00:06:08.030 align:middle line:90%
The word comes from the Greek.

00:06:08.030 --> 00:06:10.310 align:middle line:84%
The ancient Greek
esoterikos, which

00:06:10.310 --> 00:06:13.490 align:middle line:84%
is an objective, which
basically means "interior."

00:06:13.490 --> 00:06:15.780 align:middle line:84%
It means something
that is inner.

00:06:15.780 --> 00:06:18.230 align:middle line:84%
So something that is
inside, as opposed

00:06:18.230 --> 00:06:21.010 align:middle line:90%
to something that is outside.

00:06:21.010 --> 00:06:23.450 align:middle line:10%
And in ancient Greece the
term was used especially

00:06:23.450 --> 00:06:26.450 align:middle line:10%
to refer to philosophy,
to philosophical schools.

00:06:26.450 --> 00:06:28.580 align:middle line:10%
For instance, in
the case of Plato,

00:06:28.580 --> 00:06:30.770 align:middle line:10%
in the case of
Aristotle, the idea

00:06:30.770 --> 00:06:33.530 align:middle line:10%
was that there was a
particular teaching that

00:06:33.530 --> 00:06:35.600 align:middle line:10%
was meant for a broader public.

00:06:35.600 --> 00:06:38.895 align:middle line:84%
And then there was a more
restrictive kind of teaching.

00:06:38.895 --> 00:06:42.080 align:middle line:84%
And that teaching
would be reserved only

00:06:42.080 --> 00:06:43.910 align:middle line:90%
for a particular elite.

00:06:43.910 --> 00:06:46.398 align:middle line:84%
So you really needed
to be a pupil.

00:06:46.398 --> 00:06:51.340 align:middle line:90%


00:06:51.340 --> 00:06:54.460 align:middle line:90%
>> That's Hermes Trismegistus.

00:06:54.460 --> 00:06:57.880 align:middle line:90%
That's called filius noster.

00:06:57.880 --> 00:07:03.520 align:middle line:84%
And here you see the Sun,
the Moon and coming together,

00:07:03.520 --> 00:07:06.340 align:middle line:84%
it brings forward
Hermes Trismegistus.

00:07:06.340 --> 00:07:10.120 align:middle line:84%
He's having can you
say this, and it

00:07:10.120 --> 00:07:13.470 align:middle line:90%
is the symbol of initiate.

00:07:13.470 --> 00:07:19.046 align:middle line:84%
The [INAUDIBLE],, the cloak,
an attribute of power.

00:07:19.046 --> 00:07:23.490 align:middle line:84%
The text of Hermes Trismegistus
are written down already

00:07:23.490 --> 00:07:27.560 align:middle line:84%
in the pyramids of
Sakkara in Egypt.

00:07:27.560 --> 00:07:31.000 align:middle line:10%
>> We have an exhibition
on Hermes Trismegistus And

00:07:31.000 --> 00:07:34.990 align:middle line:10%
the visual imagery
connected with Hermes,

00:07:34.990 --> 00:07:39.390 align:middle line:10%
a very colorful exhibition that
shows you the roots of Hermes

00:07:39.390 --> 00:07:40.190 align:middle line:10%
Trismegistus.

00:07:40.190 --> 00:07:43.500 align:middle line:90%
He is part Egyptian, part Greek.

00:07:43.500 --> 00:07:46.420 align:middle line:84%
He is the Egyptian god
Thoth and the Greek Hermes.

00:07:46.420 --> 00:07:49.920 align:middle line:10%
And these two combined
were Hermes Trismegistus.

00:07:49.920 --> 00:07:53.800 align:middle line:10%
This is a beautiful image
of Hermes Trismegistus.

00:07:53.800 --> 00:07:57.700 align:middle line:10%
It's a reproduction
from a mosaic in Sienna.

00:07:57.700 --> 00:08:03.250 align:middle line:84%
He is a wisdom teacher, a sage
who presents to the Egyptians

00:08:03.250 --> 00:08:05.140 align:middle line:90%
the laws and the letters.

00:08:05.140 --> 00:08:07.180 align:middle line:84%
>> Originally the
distinction, perhaps,

00:08:07.180 --> 00:08:10.270 align:middle line:84%
did not have much to
do with spirituality.

00:08:10.270 --> 00:08:14.830 align:middle line:84%
Later on this idea was
connected to the ancient mystery

00:08:14.830 --> 00:08:19.750 align:middle line:84%
cults like [INAUDIBLE] or
the Mysteries of Eleusis.

00:08:19.750 --> 00:08:21.910 align:middle line:10%
And therefore a more
spiritual meaning

00:08:21.910 --> 00:08:23.500 align:middle line:10%
was attached to the word.

00:08:23.500 --> 00:08:27.940 align:middle line:10%
And it was thought that in
fact, an esoteric teaching

00:08:27.940 --> 00:08:32.049 align:middle line:10%
had to do with something
that was religious, something

00:08:32.049 --> 00:08:33.250 align:middle line:10%
that was spiritual.

00:08:33.250 --> 00:08:37.750 align:middle line:84%
So it had to do, for instance,
with the destiny of man

00:08:37.750 --> 00:08:39.520 align:middle line:90%
after death.

00:08:39.520 --> 00:08:43.419 align:middle line:84%
That is basically the
origin of the modern concept

00:08:43.419 --> 00:08:45.190 align:middle line:90%
of esotericism.

00:08:45.190 --> 00:08:48.160 align:middle line:84%
>> This is one of the most
important books in our library,

00:08:48.160 --> 00:08:52.610 align:middle line:84%
a book by Hermes Trismegistus,
the name giver of the library

00:08:52.610 --> 00:08:53.410 align:middle line:90%
of course.

00:08:53.410 --> 00:08:54.760 align:middle line:90%
Hermes.

00:08:54.760 --> 00:08:59.830 align:middle line:84%
And we collect all the editions
of his philosophical works.

00:08:59.830 --> 00:09:03.070 align:middle line:84%
We call it now the
Corpus Hermeticum.

00:09:03.070 --> 00:09:06.040 align:middle line:84%
In the older days it
was called Pimandre,

00:09:06.040 --> 00:09:10.130 align:middle line:84%
after the pupil that is
instructed by the philosopher

00:09:10.130 --> 00:09:10.930 align:middle line:90%
Hermes.

00:09:10.930 --> 00:09:28.570 align:middle line:90%


00:09:28.570 --> 00:09:30.840 align:middle line:84%
>> The Egyptian god Thoth,
and the Greek Hermes,

00:09:30.840 --> 00:09:34.150 align:middle line:84%
they are both
scribes, messengers.

00:09:34.150 --> 00:09:37.030 align:middle line:84%
And magic is also attributed
to the two of them.

00:09:37.030 --> 00:09:39.670 align:middle line:10%
And that is why they
were conflated and became

00:09:39.670 --> 00:09:42.940 align:middle line:10%
Hermes Trismegistus,
the thrice greatest.

00:09:42.940 --> 00:09:46.240 align:middle line:84%
>> Classical culture becomes
less prominent during

00:09:46.240 --> 00:09:47.200 align:middle line:90%
the Middle Ages.

00:09:47.200 --> 00:09:49.165 align:middle line:10%
Greek culture was
sort of forgotten.

00:09:49.165 --> 00:09:51.790 align:middle line:84%
But then it comes back
in the Renaissance.

00:09:51.790 --> 00:09:55.750 align:middle line:84%
>> One of the treasures of
the library is the Corpus

00:09:55.750 --> 00:09:59.650 align:middle line:84%
Hermeticum of Hermes
Trismegistus, on vellum.

00:09:59.650 --> 00:10:04.866 align:middle line:90%


00:10:04.866 --> 00:10:06.240 align:middle line:10%
>> At the end of
the Middle Ages,

00:10:06.240 --> 00:10:08.500 align:middle line:10%
with the conquest
of Constantinople,

00:10:08.500 --> 00:10:12.520 align:middle line:10%
there is the rediscovery of
the Neoplatonic texts and texts

00:10:12.520 --> 00:10:16.630 align:middle line:10%
by Plato, so the rediscovery
of Platonic philosophy.

00:10:16.630 --> 00:10:19.570 align:middle line:84%
But also the rediscovery
of the hermetic texts,

00:10:19.570 --> 00:10:23.620 align:middle line:84%
which played really a
key role in the revival

00:10:23.620 --> 00:10:27.240 align:middle line:84%
of what we call esoteric
ideas, especially in Italy.

00:10:27.240 --> 00:10:31.600 align:middle line:10%
In Florence, more particularly,
with Cosimo de Medici and then

00:10:31.600 --> 00:10:34.690 align:middle line:10%
Lorenzo Magnifico of
course, with scholars

00:10:34.690 --> 00:10:38.110 align:middle line:10%
such as Marsilio Ficino,
Piccola de la Mirandola.

00:10:38.110 --> 00:10:41.260 align:middle line:10%
It all starts in Italy but then
it's spread all around Europe.

00:10:41.260 --> 00:10:45.940 align:middle line:90%


00:10:45.940 --> 00:10:49.280 align:middle line:84%
>> I was in the Medici
library in Florence.

00:10:49.280 --> 00:10:52.510 align:middle line:84%
And it was built
by Michelangelo.

00:10:52.510 --> 00:10:57.250 align:middle line:10%
And there was an exhibition
to commemorate the 500

00:10:57.250 --> 00:11:00.790 align:middle line:10%
years since the death
of Marsilio Ficino.

00:11:00.790 --> 00:11:03.340 align:middle line:10%
The director of
the Medici library,

00:11:03.340 --> 00:11:08.280 align:middle line:10%
she said to me, Mr. Ritman,
I have a present for you.

00:11:08.280 --> 00:11:11.850 align:middle line:90%
But can't take it away.

00:11:11.850 --> 00:11:14.010 align:middle line:90%
She gave me in my hands.

00:11:14.010 --> 00:11:18.460 align:middle line:84%
And that was the original copy
of the manuscript of the Corpus

00:11:18.460 --> 00:11:19.750 align:middle line:90%
Hermeticum.

00:11:19.750 --> 00:11:22.240 align:middle line:10%
Cosimo de Medici gave an
order to Marsilio Ficino

00:11:22.240 --> 00:11:27.260 align:middle line:10%
to translate the text of
the Corpus Hermeticum.

00:11:27.260 --> 00:11:29.520 align:middle line:90%
And then it was printed.

00:11:29.520 --> 00:11:32.480 align:middle line:84%
And you see it there in
an original publication

00:11:32.480 --> 00:11:33.920 align:middle line:90%
on parchment.

00:11:33.920 --> 00:11:36.670 align:middle line:84%
>> There's also a very,
very interesting story.

00:11:36.670 --> 00:11:39.940 align:middle line:84%
When we did an exhibition
on the text and tradition

00:11:39.940 --> 00:11:43.330 align:middle line:84%
of the Corpus Hermeticum,
we had a Dutch translation

00:11:43.330 --> 00:11:46.600 align:middle line:84%
in manuscript of the
Corpus Hermeticum.

00:11:46.600 --> 00:11:50.530 align:middle line:84%
But one half of the
book was missing.

00:11:50.530 --> 00:11:54.040 align:middle line:84%
In that period I
still lived at home.

00:11:54.040 --> 00:11:56.800 align:middle line:84%
And at a certain
evening, something

00:11:56.800 --> 00:11:59.165 align:middle line:90%
was put in our postbox.

00:11:59.165 --> 00:12:00.040 align:middle line:90%
And it was a booklet.

00:12:00.040 --> 00:12:02.230 align:middle line:84%
And it said, with a
small note, Mr. Ritman,

00:12:02.230 --> 00:12:05.260 align:middle line:84%
I think you should have
this in the library.

00:12:05.260 --> 00:12:08.980 align:middle line:84%
And that was so amazing
because it was the missing part

00:12:08.980 --> 00:12:12.040 align:middle line:90%
of that same particular book.

00:12:12.040 --> 00:12:14.000 align:middle line:90%
That was reunited in this way.

00:12:14.000 --> 00:12:21.150 align:middle line:84%
And these are moments you cannot
even imagine it to happen.

00:12:21.150 --> 00:12:26.770 align:middle line:84%
And it has all happened
in the past 30 years.

00:12:26.770 --> 00:12:28.840 align:middle line:84%
>> We're talking about
Hermes Trismegistus.

00:12:28.840 --> 00:12:33.760 align:middle line:84%
And another attribute is the
ouroboros cyclical serpent

00:12:33.760 --> 00:12:35.240 align:middle line:90%
biting its own tail.

00:12:35.240 --> 00:12:40.260 align:middle line:90%


00:12:40.260 --> 00:12:43.470 align:middle line:84%
And to end with the
Staff of Hermes.

00:12:43.470 --> 00:12:46.810 align:middle line:84%
And there's a beautiful picture
at the end, an engraving,

00:12:46.810 --> 00:12:48.860 align:middle line:90%
which captures all three.

00:12:48.860 --> 00:12:51.150 align:middle line:84%
You have the Greek
Hermes on top.

00:12:51.150 --> 00:12:53.390 align:middle line:84%
In the middle it's
the hieroglyphs,

00:12:53.390 --> 00:12:54.900 align:middle line:90%
the Egyptian Thoth.

00:12:54.900 --> 00:12:57.030 align:middle line:84%
And here you have
Hermes Trismegistus

00:12:57.030 --> 00:13:01.470 align:middle line:84%
in Oriental garb, the wise
sage, the wisdom teacher.

00:13:01.470 --> 00:13:03.870 align:middle line:10%
All three are here
combined in this engraving

00:13:03.870 --> 00:13:05.532 align:middle line:10%
from the late 18th century.

00:13:05.532 --> 00:13:11.790 align:middle line:90%


00:13:11.790 --> 00:13:14.460 align:middle line:84%
>> This is one of the later
editions of the Corpus

00:13:14.460 --> 00:13:17.490 align:middle line:84%
Hermeticum, a scholarly
edition in Latin.

00:13:17.490 --> 00:13:22.680 align:middle line:84%
In other languages, such
as Italian, Dutch, English,

00:13:22.680 --> 00:13:25.920 align:middle line:84%
there are also editions
of the Corpus Hermeticum.

00:13:25.920 --> 00:13:28.590 align:middle line:84%
All the books were
very often rebound.

00:13:28.590 --> 00:13:32.550 align:middle line:84%
And not only once but
maybe four or five times.

00:13:32.550 --> 00:13:36.840 align:middle line:84%
And every time a new binding
was put around the book,

00:13:36.840 --> 00:13:41.370 align:middle line:84%
the binder cut the
paper nice and sharp.

00:13:41.370 --> 00:13:44.010 align:middle line:90%
But we lose a bit of text then.

00:13:44.010 --> 00:13:46.530 align:middle line:90%


00:13:46.530 --> 00:13:50.100 align:middle line:84%
This is the first time
the texts of Hermes

00:13:50.100 --> 00:13:52.410 align:middle line:90%
were translated into German.

00:13:52.410 --> 00:13:54.950 align:middle line:84%
And as you can see
that was rather late.

00:13:54.950 --> 00:13:57.810 align:middle line:90%
It's 1706.

00:13:57.810 --> 00:14:01.110 align:middle line:84%
Of course, everybody could
read Latin in those days.

00:14:01.110 --> 00:14:04.540 align:middle line:84%
So they kept printing
the Latin edition.

00:14:04.540 --> 00:14:07.780 align:middle line:84%
An illustration like
this, of course,

00:14:07.780 --> 00:14:09.780 align:middle line:90%
has to do with the book.

00:14:09.780 --> 00:14:17.070 align:middle line:84%
It refers to the Emerald Table,
also a text ascribed to Hermes.

00:14:17.070 --> 00:14:20.880 align:middle line:90%
And it says, so above, so below.

00:14:20.880 --> 00:14:25.980 align:middle line:84%
The macrocosmos, that the world
above, the world of the gods,

00:14:25.980 --> 00:14:29.070 align:middle line:84%
and the microcosmos,
the world of man.

00:14:29.070 --> 00:14:33.977 align:middle line:84%
>> This Corpus Hermeticum
is also having the Tabula

00:14:33.977 --> 00:14:35.670 align:middle line:90%
Smaragdina.

00:14:35.670 --> 00:14:39.690 align:middle line:84%
>> This is a beautiful engraving
from the early 17th century

00:14:39.690 --> 00:14:41.520 align:middle line:90%
called the Tabula Smaragdina.

00:14:41.520 --> 00:14:44.730 align:middle line:84%
And one of the most pregnant
phrases from this very brief

00:14:44.730 --> 00:14:48.960 align:middle line:84%
text, emerald tablet of Hermes,
is, "that which is above

00:14:48.960 --> 00:14:50.670 align:middle line:90%
is like that which is below."

00:14:50.670 --> 00:14:54.570 align:middle line:84%
And it just tells you all
about the intimate connection

00:14:54.570 --> 00:14:57.420 align:middle line:84%
between the macrocosm
and the microcosm.

00:14:57.420 --> 00:15:03.670 align:middle line:84%
>> In this period of time, many
persons are coming to an idea

00:15:03.670 --> 00:15:09.615 align:middle line:84%
that there is something hidden
behind the curtain of visible

00:15:09.615 --> 00:15:10.415 align:middle line:90%
life.

00:15:10.415 --> 00:15:13.380 align:middle line:84%
>> A hidden meaning
that has to be found.

00:15:13.380 --> 00:15:15.660 align:middle line:84%
A hidden meaning that
has been handed down

00:15:15.660 --> 00:15:19.320 align:middle line:84%
in the form of tradition,
or hidden meaning that

00:15:19.320 --> 00:15:23.940 align:middle line:84%
can be discovered through
particular experiences

00:15:23.940 --> 00:15:29.060 align:middle line:84%
of revelation, of contact with
the divine dimension with God.

00:15:29.060 --> 00:15:31.155 align:middle line:84%
Or also with nature,
for instance.

00:15:31.155 --> 00:15:34.770 align:middle line:84%
A mystical experience
of fusion with nature.

00:15:34.770 --> 00:15:37.470 align:middle line:90%
>> Let's climb the mountain.

00:15:37.470 --> 00:15:40.510 align:middle line:90%
Let's try to reach the top.

00:15:40.510 --> 00:15:45.110 align:middle line:90%
Or, let's go deep in the earth.

00:15:45.110 --> 00:15:49.610 align:middle line:84%
But what you find out
at the end of the story,

00:15:49.610 --> 00:15:53.930 align:middle line:84%
you only find at
the certain moment,

00:15:53.930 --> 00:15:58.220 align:middle line:84%
some persons will
climb to the top.

00:15:58.220 --> 00:16:03.890 align:middle line:84%
Some persons who dive
so deep in the mystery.

00:16:03.890 --> 00:16:06.770 align:middle line:84%
>> This hidden meaning can
be found in different ways,

00:16:06.770 --> 00:16:08.000 align:middle line:90%
in different places.

00:16:08.000 --> 00:16:09.740 align:middle line:90%
It can be found in the text.

00:16:09.740 --> 00:16:11.540 align:middle line:90%
For instance, the Bible.

00:16:11.540 --> 00:16:14.530 align:middle line:10%
But also all other sacred texts.

00:16:14.530 --> 00:16:16.880 align:middle line:84%
It can also be
found in the Koran.

00:16:16.880 --> 00:16:18.290 align:middle line:90%
We think about Islam.

00:16:18.290 --> 00:16:20.580 align:middle line:84%
But it can also be
found in nature.

00:16:20.580 --> 00:16:23.590 align:middle line:10%
An idea that has been widespread
since the Middle Ages--

00:16:23.590 --> 00:16:28.820 align:middle line:10%
God is speaking to us not only
through the textual revelation

00:16:28.820 --> 00:16:34.880 align:middle line:10%
of the Bible, but also through
nature when we have contact

00:16:34.880 --> 00:16:36.800 align:middle line:10%
with the natural real.

00:16:36.800 --> 00:16:38.510 align:middle line:90%
We can read symbols.

00:16:38.510 --> 00:16:39.890 align:middle line:90%
We can read signs.

00:16:39.890 --> 00:16:44.420 align:middle line:84%
And through a particular
hermeneutical ability,

00:16:44.420 --> 00:16:46.280 align:middle line:84%
which is the
ability to interpret

00:16:46.280 --> 00:16:48.680 align:middle line:84%
these signs and
these symbols, we

00:16:48.680 --> 00:16:51.080 align:middle line:84%
can understand the
hidden message.

00:16:51.080 --> 00:16:56.580 align:middle line:84%
So we can understand what
God is trying to tell us.

00:16:56.580 --> 00:17:02.080 align:middle line:84%
>> So the only thing
is to open the curtain.

00:17:02.080 --> 00:17:09.140 align:middle line:84%
And then you come in a
landscape of inner reality.

00:17:09.140 --> 00:17:16.000 align:middle line:84%
But that will not say
that you reach your goal.

00:17:16.000 --> 00:17:21.109 align:middle line:84%
The man who climbed to
the top and the man who

00:17:21.109 --> 00:17:28.434 align:middle line:84%
was diving into the water
to find that hermetic pearl.

00:17:28.434 --> 00:17:32.100 align:middle line:84%
The fantastic thing
is that he brought it

00:17:32.100 --> 00:17:37.560 align:middle line:84%
in a fish bowl
frame, that everybody

00:17:37.560 --> 00:17:40.380 align:middle line:90%
could touch the experience.

00:17:40.380 --> 00:17:43.640 align:middle line:84%
That everybody could
receive that experience.

00:17:43.640 --> 00:17:49.100 align:middle line:84%
And that is how, I would
say, so mysterious.

00:17:49.100 --> 00:17:52.350 align:middle line:84%
>> Gradually, Hermes
Trismegistus becomes really

00:17:52.350 --> 00:17:54.300 align:middle line:90%
associated with alchemy.

00:17:54.300 --> 00:17:57.120 align:middle line:84%
And he becomes the father
of all philosophers.

00:17:57.120 --> 00:17:59.520 align:middle line:84%
And the practitioners
of alchemy become

00:17:59.520 --> 00:18:02.810 align:middle line:84%
known as the sons of
Hermes, the filii hermeti.

00:18:02.810 --> 00:18:08.450 align:middle line:84%
So there's a very close bond
between Hermes and alchemy.

00:18:08.450 --> 00:18:12.120 align:middle line:84%
In this library, on these
shelves, you find alchemy.

00:18:12.120 --> 00:18:14.210 align:middle line:90%
You find hermetica.

00:18:14.210 --> 00:18:16.760 align:middle line:84%
And the two are
very much related.

00:18:16.760 --> 00:18:21.980 align:middle line:10%
Hermes is, so to speak, the
patron saint of alchemy.

00:18:21.980 --> 00:18:25.850 align:middle line:84%
In the 16th and 17th centuries,
people who performed alchemy,

00:18:25.850 --> 00:18:28.170 align:middle line:84%
alchemists, were known
as the sons of Hermes.

00:18:28.170 --> 00:18:30.290 align:middle line:84%
So there is a very
close connection

00:18:30.290 --> 00:18:32.180 align:middle line:90%
between alchemy and Hermes.

00:18:32.180 --> 00:18:34.280 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:18:34.280 --> 00:18:39.770 align:middle line:84%
>> You don't find many
alchemical symbols painted.

00:18:39.770 --> 00:18:45.540 align:middle line:84%
This is one of the great moments
also in my interest as an art

00:18:45.540 --> 00:18:46.340 align:middle line:90%
collector.

00:18:46.340 --> 00:18:49.520 align:middle line:84%
>> It shows the
triumph of alchemy.

00:18:49.520 --> 00:18:51.500 align:middle line:90%
A triumphal chariot with--

00:18:51.500 --> 00:18:53.450 align:middle line:90%
>> Basil Valentine.

00:18:53.450 --> 00:18:56.750 align:middle line:84%
>> As it has never been
reproduced and never been

00:18:56.750 --> 00:18:58.550 align:middle line:90%
looked at by scholars.

00:18:58.550 --> 00:19:02.660 align:middle line:84%
This little painting is
probably unique in the history

00:19:02.660 --> 00:19:04.670 align:middle line:90%
of alchemical imagery.

00:19:04.670 --> 00:19:08.780 align:middle line:84%
>> A lady, who is the
negative side of alchemy,

00:19:08.780 --> 00:19:13.460 align:middle line:84%
tries to attract, I would
say, the pseudo-alchemists.

00:19:13.460 --> 00:19:19.710 align:middle line:10%
All the real adepts
were taking the secrets

00:19:19.710 --> 00:19:25.650 align:middle line:10%
of the keys of Basil Valentine
to the real process of alchemy.

00:19:25.650 --> 00:19:31.080 align:middle line:84%
>> I only recognized it because
I was looking in an old book.

00:19:31.080 --> 00:19:34.410 align:middle line:90%
And there it was redrawn.

00:19:34.410 --> 00:19:37.890 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, I
recognized this drawing.

00:19:37.890 --> 00:19:40.560 align:middle line:84%
This is the picture
that Mr. Ritman

00:19:40.560 --> 00:19:43.680 align:middle line:84%
has hanging on his
wall for 20 years.

00:19:43.680 --> 00:19:47.130 align:middle line:84%
And then I took a closer
look and found out what

00:19:47.130 --> 00:19:50.590 align:middle line:84%
an extremely rare
piece we have here.

00:19:50.590 --> 00:20:01.860 align:middle line:90%


00:20:01.860 --> 00:20:06.690 align:middle line:84%
>> For me, the imagery of
the library is so interesting

00:20:06.690 --> 00:20:12.060 align:middle line:84%
because the symbolic engravings
and drawings that you will find

00:20:12.060 --> 00:20:16.710 align:middle line:84%
in many books of this library,
they contain the same elements.

00:20:16.710 --> 00:20:20.880 align:middle line:84%
Like the circle and the
square and the triangle.

00:20:20.880 --> 00:20:25.260 align:middle line:84%
And their meaning is,
in fact, universal.

00:20:25.260 --> 00:20:30.570 align:middle line:10%
But there is endless ways that
these symbols can be applied,

00:20:30.570 --> 00:20:33.420 align:middle line:10%
whether in the work of
Christian Kabbalists

00:20:33.420 --> 00:20:36.170 align:middle line:10%
or in the works of
a mystic like Jakob

00:20:36.170 --> 00:20:40.950 align:middle line:10%
Boehme or a Christian hermetic
thinker as Robert Fludd.

00:20:40.950 --> 00:20:43.350 align:middle line:90%
>> I was always very curious.

00:20:43.350 --> 00:20:46.790 align:middle line:84%
I was never satisfied
with explanations.

00:20:46.790 --> 00:20:53.300 align:middle line:84%
And I said to myself,
let me go and look

00:20:53.300 --> 00:20:55.450 align:middle line:90%
to the reality of things.

00:20:55.450 --> 00:20:58.950 align:middle line:84%
And therefore, I
knew, that I was

00:20:58.950 --> 00:21:04.470 align:middle line:84%
a spark between the
invisible life as a spark

00:21:04.470 --> 00:21:07.740 align:middle line:90%
and then disappear again.

00:21:07.740 --> 00:21:10.050 align:middle line:90%
Mr. Ritman disappeared.

00:21:10.050 --> 00:21:15.300 align:middle line:84%
So I ask myself, when I am
only a spark, a light flash

00:21:15.300 --> 00:21:23.260 align:middle line:84%
in a moment, why I should not
build a library of awareness,

00:21:23.260 --> 00:21:24.420 align:middle line:90%
of research.

00:21:24.420 --> 00:21:29.910 align:middle line:10%
I started this library
with the hermetic science.

00:21:29.910 --> 00:21:34.770 align:middle line:84%
The hermetic science is a
science of all awareness.

00:21:34.770 --> 00:21:38.770 align:middle line:90%


00:21:38.770 --> 00:21:41.810 align:middle line:90%
I am convinced.

00:21:41.810 --> 00:21:48.090 align:middle line:84%
With the Hermetic tradition,
you come into contact

00:21:48.090 --> 00:21:52.310 align:middle line:84%
not only with people,
but also with religions,

00:21:52.310 --> 00:21:56.370 align:middle line:84%
with mystery schools,
with initiates.

00:21:56.370 --> 00:22:02.070 align:middle line:84%
And for me, the mystery
schools around the world,

00:22:02.070 --> 00:22:05.920 align:middle line:84%
they connected to
the master plan

00:22:05.920 --> 00:22:11.460 align:middle line:84%
and with the flow of
human awareness through,

00:22:11.460 --> 00:22:14.230 align:middle line:90%
I would say, the millenniums.

00:22:14.230 --> 00:22:20.420 align:middle line:84%
This millennium is a
completely different paradigm

00:22:20.420 --> 00:22:26.610 align:middle line:84%
of references than what we
saw, so far, in the last 5,000

00:22:26.610 --> 00:22:27.720 align:middle line:90%
years.

00:22:27.720 --> 00:22:30.450 align:middle line:84%
Different developments
of religion.

00:22:30.450 --> 00:22:33.220 align:middle line:84%
Different developments
of spirituality.

00:22:33.220 --> 00:22:40.180 align:middle line:84%
And now it comes together
in one global goal.

00:22:40.180 --> 00:22:43.500 align:middle line:90%
And that is, for me, gnosis.

00:22:43.500 --> 00:22:44.890 align:middle line:90%
Gnosis.

00:22:44.890 --> 00:22:49.380 align:middle line:84%
Hermeticism, agnosticism,
they have the same roots

00:22:49.380 --> 00:22:53.290 align:middle line:84%
in all the stories, in all
the religions of the world.

00:22:53.290 --> 00:22:59.680 align:middle line:84%
It has to do with, I
don't want to call it God.

00:22:59.680 --> 00:23:03.060 align:middle line:90%
But I want to call it Creator.

00:23:03.060 --> 00:23:04.950 align:middle line:90%
Creation.

00:23:04.950 --> 00:23:08.430 align:middle line:90%
And creation and men.

00:23:08.430 --> 00:23:14.930 align:middle line:84%
The three aspects of, I
would say, the divine.

00:23:14.930 --> 00:23:17.400 align:middle line:90%
The element of nature.

00:23:17.400 --> 00:23:21.100 align:middle line:84%
The two elements of nature,
the male and the female,

00:23:21.100 --> 00:23:26.370 align:middle line:90%
come together in a macrocosm.

00:23:26.370 --> 00:23:30.970 align:middle line:84%
>> Gnosis is the third component
of our European cultural

00:23:30.970 --> 00:23:31.877 align:middle line:90%
heritage.

00:23:31.877 --> 00:23:33.710 align:middle line:84%
And that's what we have
here in the library.

00:23:33.710 --> 00:23:36.210 align:middle line:90%
[CHANTING MUSIC]

00:23:36.210 --> 00:23:45.650 align:middle line:90%


00:23:45.650 --> 00:23:47.170 align:middle line:90%
>> Gnosticism.

00:23:47.170 --> 00:23:49.990 align:middle line:84%
They speak about
light and darkness.

00:23:49.990 --> 00:23:55.300 align:middle line:84%
The point in Hermeticism
is that they don't reject

00:23:55.300 --> 00:23:58.390 align:middle line:90%
the gnostic approach of life.

00:23:58.390 --> 00:24:04.520 align:middle line:84%
But they say it is the
task of a human being,

00:24:04.520 --> 00:24:10.130 align:middle line:84%
through daily experience
in your life, where

00:24:10.130 --> 00:24:17.080 align:middle line:84%
you meet positive and
negative influences,

00:24:17.080 --> 00:24:22.290 align:middle line:84%
to come to the point that they
are always going together.

00:24:22.290 --> 00:24:23.530 align:middle line:90%
That they have a meaning.

00:24:23.530 --> 00:24:27.830 align:middle line:84%
If we don't see that
this library has meaning,

00:24:27.830 --> 00:24:33.010 align:middle line:84%
if we don't see that the
last 12,000 years are also

00:24:33.010 --> 00:24:39.200 align:middle line:84%
a reflection of the waves of
life, if we don't see that,

00:24:39.200 --> 00:24:41.380 align:middle line:84%
then we don't come to a
point of concentration.

00:24:41.380 --> 00:24:47.660 align:middle line:84%
And so this library is a
point of concentration.

00:24:47.660 --> 00:24:51.380 align:middle line:84%
>> Of all the books
in the Ritman Library,

00:24:51.380 --> 00:24:57.320 align:middle line:84%
I love the hermetic
books most because to me,

00:24:57.320 --> 00:25:02.330 align:middle line:84%
this hermetic worldview, the
relation between god, kosmos,

00:25:02.330 --> 00:25:08.450 align:middle line:84%
man, is the essence of
human consciousness.

00:25:08.450 --> 00:25:13.970 align:middle line:84%
That's the universal aspect in
all religious and philosophical

00:25:13.970 --> 00:25:14.790 align:middle line:90%
traditions.

00:25:14.790 --> 00:25:18.860 align:middle line:84%
And what's most important
is that a human being, him

00:25:18.860 --> 00:25:21.020 align:middle line:90%
or herself, it's about us.

00:25:21.020 --> 00:25:21.990 align:middle line:90%
It's about you.

00:25:21.990 --> 00:25:23.400 align:middle line:90%
It's about me.

00:25:23.400 --> 00:25:25.550 align:middle line:84%
In the hermetic
tradition it's said,

00:25:25.550 --> 00:25:29.170 align:middle line:84%
when you want to know
God, know yourself.

00:25:29.170 --> 00:25:30.350 align:middle line:90%
Study nature.

00:25:30.350 --> 00:25:33.290 align:middle line:10%
And you will know God.

00:25:33.290 --> 00:25:38.970 align:middle line:84%
>> The only reason that
everything is not OK is that we

00:25:38.970 --> 00:25:40.860 align:middle line:90%
lack knowledge.

00:25:40.860 --> 00:25:45.070 align:middle line:84%
Knowledge of a
dimension that we don't

00:25:45.070 --> 00:25:47.760 align:middle line:90%
bring into our daily practice.

00:25:47.760 --> 00:25:49.870 align:middle line:90%
The gnosis is ours.

00:25:49.870 --> 00:25:52.930 align:middle line:90%
It is an energy field.

00:25:52.930 --> 00:25:58.360 align:middle line:84%
What we don't use together, that
is the misuse of the spirit.

00:25:58.360 --> 00:26:03.050 align:middle line:84%
That we are only living,
that we are consumers,

00:26:03.050 --> 00:26:06.398 align:middle line:90%
but that we are not soul beings.

00:26:06.398 --> 00:26:08.888 align:middle line:90%
[PIANO MUSIC]

00:26:08.888 --> 00:26:17.290 align:middle line:90%


00:26:17.290 --> 00:26:18.090 align:middle line:10%
>> Kabbalah.

00:26:18.090 --> 00:26:21.370 align:middle line:10%
Jewish forms of mysticism
and esotericism,

00:26:21.370 --> 00:26:24.090 align:middle line:10%
begin in the late
Middle Ages, especially

00:26:24.090 --> 00:26:27.980 align:middle line:10%
in the South of France and
also in those areas that

00:26:27.980 --> 00:26:33.540 align:middle line:10%
were a kind of crossroad between
Islamic, Christian and Jewish

00:26:33.540 --> 00:26:35.140 align:middle line:10%
culture, especially in Spain.

00:26:35.140 --> 00:26:54.570 align:middle line:90%


00:26:54.570 --> 00:26:58.570 align:middle line:84%
Some authors in this period
construct a whole system

00:26:58.570 --> 00:27:02.140 align:middle line:84%
of occult philosophy, which
is a kind of synthesis effect.

00:27:02.140 --> 00:27:07.880 align:middle line:90%


00:27:07.880 --> 00:27:09.830 align:middle line:84%
Heinrich Cornelius
Agrippa, for instance,

00:27:09.830 --> 00:27:14.750 align:middle line:84%
writes a famous work called
The Occulta Philosophia, where

00:27:14.750 --> 00:27:17.320 align:middle line:84%
