But we also have
knowledge of God.

01:11:13.640 --> 01:11:14.670 align:middle line:90%
Inner knowledge.

01:11:14.670 --> 01:11:16.610 align:middle line:84%
The Corpus Hermeticum
also says it.

01:11:16.610 --> 01:11:19.700 align:middle line:84%
That is why man is the
most gifted of creatures.

01:11:19.700 --> 01:11:23.510 align:middle line:84%
Because he has the use of
his five senses but also he

01:11:23.510 --> 01:11:24.350 align:middle line:90%
has gnosis.

01:11:24.350 --> 01:11:27.020 align:middle line:84%
He can achieve a
knowledge of God.

01:11:27.020 --> 01:11:30.210 align:middle line:84%
And that is what this
image is also all about.

01:11:30.210 --> 01:11:31.583 align:middle line:90%
Omnia [INAUDIBLE].

01:11:31.583 --> 01:11:35.170 align:middle line:90%
Everything from the one.

01:11:35.170 --> 01:11:36.800 align:middle line:90%
Omnia ad unum.

01:11:36.800 --> 01:11:39.390 align:middle line:90%
Everything returns in the one.

01:11:39.390 --> 01:11:47.790 align:middle line:84%
>> Everything through the unity
brings everything to the unity.

01:11:47.790 --> 01:11:50.870 align:middle line:90%
So here you have the creator.

01:11:50.870 --> 01:11:52.280 align:middle line:90%
You have the nature.

01:11:52.280 --> 01:11:54.020 align:middle line:84%
And here you have
the waves of life.

01:11:54.020 --> 01:11:58.010 align:middle line:84%
And everything comes
together in the microcosmos.

01:11:58.010 --> 01:12:00.420 align:middle line:90%
[CHANTING MUSIC]

01:12:00.420 --> 01:12:16.580 align:middle line:90%


01:12:16.580 --> 01:12:19.190 align:middle line:84%
>> The phenomenon of
western esotericism can be

01:12:19.190 --> 01:12:23.450 align:middle line:84%
characterized by the fact that
in most historical periods it

01:12:23.450 --> 01:12:28.990 align:middle line:84%
seems to be at odds with
mainstream religious thinking.

01:12:28.990 --> 01:12:30.860 align:middle line:84%
And then later,
especially starting

01:12:30.860 --> 01:12:33.320 align:middle line:84%
with the scientific
revolution and with the period

01:12:33.320 --> 01:12:37.100 align:middle line:84%
of the Enlightenment, also
with scientific and rational

01:12:37.100 --> 01:12:37.940 align:middle line:90%
thinking.

01:12:37.940 --> 01:12:42.910 align:middle line:84%
>> The library is a telescope
of visions of thousands

01:12:42.910 --> 01:12:45.780 align:middle line:90%
of persons.

01:12:45.780 --> 01:12:49.470 align:middle line:84%
But my life itself, my
inner life, is a microscope.

01:12:49.470 --> 01:12:52.470 align:middle line:10%
>> Perhaps an author you
might not expect to find

01:12:52.470 --> 01:12:54.930 align:middle line:10%
on the shelves of this
library, which is a hermetic,

01:12:54.930 --> 01:12:58.520 align:middle line:10%
alchemical, magical
library, is Spinoza.

01:12:58.520 --> 01:13:00.600 align:middle line:90%
And but he is here.

01:13:00.600 --> 01:13:04.080 align:middle line:84%
This is an edition of one
of his most famous works,

01:13:04.080 --> 01:13:06.650 align:middle line:84%
the Tractatus
Theologico Politicus.

01:13:06.650 --> 01:13:09.560 align:middle line:90%
It's an amazing work in itself.

01:13:09.560 --> 01:13:12.350 align:middle line:84%
It's also a very
special edition.

01:13:12.350 --> 01:13:15.740 align:middle line:84%
As you can see it was
supposedly printed in Hamburg.

01:13:15.740 --> 01:13:17.460 align:middle line:84%
But it wasn't printed
in Hamburg at all.

01:13:17.460 --> 01:13:19.340 align:middle line:90%
It was printed in Amsterdam.

01:13:19.340 --> 01:13:21.980 align:middle line:84%
Amsterdam in the 17th
century was a great city

01:13:21.980 --> 01:13:24.260 align:middle line:84%
for freedom of expression,
freedom of the press.

01:13:24.260 --> 01:13:26.690 align:middle line:84%
Spinoza was very well
aware of the fact

01:13:26.690 --> 01:13:28.690 align:middle line:84%
that this was a
very explosive work.

01:13:28.690 --> 01:13:29.780 align:middle line:90%
It's in Latin.

01:13:29.780 --> 01:13:33.780 align:middle line:84%
It's international, Latin
being the Lingua Franca.

01:13:33.780 --> 01:13:36.890 align:middle line:84%
And we have a letter from
Spinoza to a friend of his.

01:13:36.890 --> 01:13:39.620 align:middle line:84%
And he says, don't
publish the work in Dutch

01:13:39.620 --> 01:13:42.800 align:middle line:84%
because the ministers,
the preachers,

01:13:42.800 --> 01:13:44.660 align:middle line:84%
are already up in
arms against me.

01:13:44.660 --> 01:13:47.900 align:middle line:84%
And if this work becomes
available in Dutch

01:13:47.900 --> 01:13:50.160 align:middle line:90%
I will have no end of trouble.

01:13:50.160 --> 01:13:52.650 align:middle line:84%
So the Dutch translation
of the Tractatus

01:13:52.650 --> 01:13:56.862 align:middle line:84%
was only published in 1693
when Spinoza was long dead.

01:13:56.862 --> 01:13:59.840 align:middle line:90%
[CLASSICAL MUSIC]

01:13:59.840 --> 01:14:02.900 align:middle line:84%
>> This kind of conflictual
relationship should not be

01:14:02.900 --> 01:14:06.680 align:middle line:84%
overemphasized in the
sense that, in many cases,

01:14:06.680 --> 01:14:10.160 align:middle line:84%
you see that authors are
trying to find a compromise.

01:14:10.160 --> 01:14:14.630 align:middle line:10%
And if we move a little bit
later, to the 18th century,

01:14:14.630 --> 01:14:17.570 align:middle line:10%
we encounter another very
important phenomenon,

01:14:17.570 --> 01:14:20.000 align:middle line:10%
which is modern Freemasonry.

01:14:20.000 --> 01:14:22.280 align:middle line:10%
And that's very important
because although we already

01:14:22.280 --> 01:14:25.190 align:middle line:10%
see this model earlier
on with the beginning

01:14:25.190 --> 01:14:28.420 align:middle line:10%
of Rosicrucianism-- so, the
idea that in fact, esotericists

01:14:28.420 --> 01:14:30.620 align:middle line:10%
don't work alone.

01:14:30.620 --> 01:14:32.420 align:middle line:84%
That, in fact, they
should be organized

01:14:32.420 --> 01:14:35.880 align:middle line:84%
in some sort of brotherhood,
some sort of fraternity kind

01:14:35.880 --> 01:14:36.680 align:middle line:90%
of organization.

01:14:36.680 --> 01:14:38.510 align:middle line:90%
[SOFT MUSIC]

01:14:38.510 --> 01:14:41.970 align:middle line:84%
But with Rosicrucianism it's
not clear whether this was just

01:14:41.970 --> 01:14:42.770 align:middle line:90%
a project--

01:14:42.770 --> 01:14:46.040 align:middle line:84%
something that was on paper--
or whether such an organization

01:14:46.040 --> 01:14:47.570 align:middle line:90%
really existed.

01:14:47.570 --> 01:14:52.010 align:middle line:84%
Well, with Freemasonry, we have
a real, concrete organization

01:14:52.010 --> 01:14:53.200 align:middle line:90%
that is being created.

01:14:53.200 --> 01:14:56.510 align:middle line:84%
So people getting
together and engaging

01:14:56.510 --> 01:14:59.990 align:middle line:84%
in all sorts of communal
activities and rituals

01:14:59.990 --> 01:15:01.010 align:middle line:90%
and so on.

01:15:01.010 --> 01:15:03.560 align:middle line:84%
>> We had famous
visitors in the past.

01:15:03.560 --> 01:15:07.495 align:middle line:84%
Umberto Eco, who is also a
great collector of hermetic

01:15:07.495 --> 01:15:09.110 align:middle line:90%
and alchemical works.

01:15:09.110 --> 01:15:12.350 align:middle line:10%
Last year we had Dan
Brown, who was totally

01:15:12.350 --> 01:15:16.250 align:middle line:10%
amazed by this
collection because he

01:15:16.250 --> 01:15:20.870 align:middle line:10%
has written so many novels
about Rosicrucians, Freemasons.

01:15:20.870 --> 01:15:24.540 align:middle line:84%
So he was bowled over by
his visit to the library.

01:15:24.540 --> 01:15:25.340 align:middle line:90%
[CLASSICAL MUSIC]

01:15:25.340 --> 01:15:28.970 align:middle line:84%
>> One should not think that
Freemasonry is esoteric,

01:15:28.970 --> 01:15:32.480 align:middle line:84%
per se, because Freemasonry
in fact is a very complex

01:15:32.480 --> 01:15:33.560 align:middle line:90%
phenomenon.

01:15:33.560 --> 01:15:36.200 align:middle line:84%
And there are traditions
in Freemasonry

01:15:36.200 --> 01:15:40.760 align:middle line:84%
that are more open to
esotericism, to spirituality,

01:15:40.760 --> 01:15:42.440 align:middle line:84%
and other traditions
that perhaps

01:15:42.440 --> 01:15:45.550 align:middle line:84%
prefer to have a kind of
more rational approach

01:15:45.550 --> 01:15:46.903 align:middle line:90%
to spirituality.

01:15:46.903 --> 01:15:49.368 align:middle line:90%
[OPERA SINGING]

01:15:49.368 --> 01:16:04.170 align:middle line:90%


01:16:04.170 --> 01:16:10.810 align:middle line:84%
>> The microcosmos is a spark
of the Big Bang in the Big Bang.

01:16:10.810 --> 01:16:14.590 align:middle line:10%
It's the god's
particle in creation.

01:16:14.590 --> 01:16:22.370 align:middle line:84%
And I carry that god's particle
as a treasure in my life.

01:16:22.370 --> 01:16:23.330 align:middle line:90%
[PIANO MUSIC]

01:16:23.330 --> 01:16:26.390 align:middle line:84%
>> The library is so special
because it's a private library

01:16:26.390 --> 01:16:28.040 align:middle line:90%
but it's open to the public.

01:16:28.040 --> 01:16:30.590 align:middle line:84%
And it has on the
shelves authors

01:16:30.590 --> 01:16:34.310 align:middle line:84%
who wanted to unite people
and bring them together.

01:16:34.310 --> 01:16:35.600 align:middle line:90%
Who didn't want division.

01:16:35.600 --> 01:16:37.730 align:middle line:84%
Who didn't want
religious strife.

01:16:37.730 --> 01:16:41.360 align:middle line:84%
Who wanted people to
acknowledge, to realize,

01:16:41.360 --> 01:16:44.330 align:middle line:84%
that they are a
mirror of nature,

01:16:44.330 --> 01:16:47.030 align:middle line:90%
that they are the microcosm.

01:16:47.030 --> 01:16:50.350 align:middle line:84%
That great hermetic
sentence-- as above, so below.

01:16:50.350 --> 01:16:55.150 align:middle line:90%
>> Man is a mirror of light.

01:16:55.150 --> 01:16:58.180 align:middle line:90%
He has a task of connection.

01:16:58.180 --> 01:17:02.522 align:middle line:90%
So to receive that energy.

01:17:02.522 --> 01:17:04.480 align:middle line:84%
>> The 18th century, of
course, is also the Age

01:17:04.480 --> 01:17:06.354 align:middle line:84%
of the Enlightenment,
which should be the age

01:17:06.354 --> 01:17:07.330 align:middle line:90%
of rationality.

01:17:07.330 --> 01:17:09.610 align:middle line:84%
It insists on the
importance of reason

01:17:09.610 --> 01:17:11.170 align:middle line:90%
and the importance of science.

01:17:11.170 --> 01:17:13.720 align:middle line:84%
It sees at the same
time the development

01:17:13.720 --> 01:17:16.540 align:middle line:84%
of another esoteric
current which

01:17:16.540 --> 01:17:20.590 align:middle line:84%
also makes a reference to the
symbol of the light, which

01:17:20.590 --> 01:17:22.250 align:middle line:90%
is called illuminism.

01:17:22.250 --> 01:17:25.930 align:middle line:84%
>> There is a direct
energy floating throughout

01:17:25.930 --> 01:17:27.280 align:middle line:90%
the universe.

01:17:27.280 --> 01:17:29.920 align:middle line:90%
The simple example, light.

01:17:29.920 --> 01:17:34.090 align:middle line:90%
Light in itself is invisible.

01:17:34.090 --> 01:17:37.960 align:middle line:10%
But at the moment that it
comes into contact with matter

01:17:37.960 --> 01:17:41.350 align:middle line:10%
it becomes color
and becomes life.

01:17:41.350 --> 01:17:46.910 align:middle line:84%
And we can say the Sun
is the origin of light.

01:17:46.910 --> 01:17:51.980 align:middle line:84%
But light in itself, of
the Sun, is invisible.

01:17:51.980 --> 01:17:55.360 align:middle line:84%
>> Illuminism lays great
emphasis on the idea

01:17:55.360 --> 01:17:56.660 align:middle line:90%
of mystical knowledge.

01:17:56.660 --> 01:18:00.140 align:middle line:84%
A based mystical approach to
nature and to the mysteries

01:18:00.140 --> 01:18:01.970 align:middle line:84%
of the universe,
which is perhaps

01:18:01.970 --> 01:18:04.850 align:middle line:84%
the kind of flip side
of the Enlightenment.

01:18:04.850 --> 01:18:08.360 align:middle line:84%
>> My father decided he wanted
to make his private collection

01:18:08.360 --> 01:18:12.360 align:middle line:90%
publicly accessible in '84.

01:18:12.360 --> 01:18:15.990 align:middle line:84%
He had the vision to
immediately say, OK.

01:18:15.990 --> 01:18:20.880 align:middle line:84%
When we open up this collection,
which is in fact a knowledge

01:18:20.880 --> 01:18:25.800 align:middle line:84%
field, it should be
accessed in a scholarly way.

01:18:25.800 --> 01:18:29.220 align:middle line:10%
>> I built my library.

01:18:29.220 --> 01:18:33.640 align:middle line:90%
I built the Research Institute.

01:18:33.640 --> 01:18:40.040 align:middle line:10%
I was everywhere together
with my staff in exhibitions.

01:18:40.040 --> 01:18:44.510 align:middle line:84%
I published many books
about this field.

01:18:44.510 --> 01:18:48.760 align:middle line:84%
And now I want to come to a
certain point that we say,

01:18:48.760 --> 01:18:51.970 align:middle line:90%
let us share the future.

01:18:51.970 --> 01:18:56.240 align:middle line:10%
>> We want to build a global
hermetic circle of people who

01:18:56.240 --> 01:18:58.090 align:middle line:10%
are genuinely interested.

01:18:58.090 --> 01:19:01.540 align:middle line:84%
We started the project
Hermetically Open

01:19:01.540 --> 01:19:05.830 align:middle line:84%
to share every
activity and aspect

01:19:05.830 --> 01:19:10.360 align:middle line:84%
that we do with the collection
in exhibitions and projects

01:19:10.360 --> 01:19:13.510 align:middle line:84%
and the Ritman Institute
and our publishing

01:19:13.510 --> 01:19:14.710 align:middle line:90%
house in the Pelikaan.

01:19:14.710 --> 01:19:16.420 align:middle line:10%
>> Simple.

01:19:16.420 --> 01:19:17.250 align:middle line:10%
Brief.

01:19:17.250 --> 01:19:18.050 align:middle line:10%
Clear.

01:19:18.050 --> 01:19:19.510 align:middle line:90%
Transparent.

01:19:19.510 --> 01:19:23.260 align:middle line:84%
Not to come with answers
that people don't understand.

01:19:23.260 --> 01:19:27.430 align:middle line:84%
>> Hermetically Open to all
has in fact, after a few years,

01:19:27.430 --> 01:19:33.940 align:middle line:84%
become our main strategy as a
library because we have quite

01:19:33.940 --> 01:19:37.660 align:middle line:84%
an elaborate scholarly context
we have established over

01:19:37.660 --> 01:19:38.950 align:middle line:90%
the years.

01:19:38.950 --> 01:19:42.730 align:middle line:10%
And we see that it's
important that we open up

01:19:42.730 --> 01:19:44.980 align:middle line:10%
all this knowledge,
all this expertise,

01:19:44.980 --> 01:19:45.955 align:middle line:10%
to a broader audience.

01:19:45.955 --> 01:19:48.080 align:middle line:84%
And not only share
our collection

01:19:48.080 --> 01:19:51.520 align:middle line:84%
but also share our
expertise in this way.

01:19:51.520 --> 01:19:55.390 align:middle line:84%
>> I always saw the total
field in front of me.

01:19:55.390 --> 01:19:56.785 align:middle line:90%
And then the books came.

01:19:56.785 --> 01:19:59.510 align:middle line:84%
The field of
magnetism, of energy.

01:19:59.510 --> 01:20:00.310 align:middle line:90%
[PIANO MUSIC]

01:20:00.310 --> 01:20:03.580 align:middle line:84%
>> At the end of the 18th
century we have the current

01:20:03.580 --> 01:20:07.050 align:middle line:84%
of animal magnetism
with Franz Anton Mesmer.

01:20:07.050 --> 01:20:10.540 align:middle line:84%
And another important
current is Swedenborgianism,

01:20:10.540 --> 01:20:13.750 align:middle line:84%
based on the teachings
of the Swedish visionary

01:20:13.750 --> 01:20:15.610 align:middle line:90%
and mystic Emanuel Swedenborg.

01:20:15.610 --> 01:20:17.350 align:middle line:90%
These two currents combined--

01:20:17.350 --> 01:20:20.560 align:middle line:84%
Swedenborgianism and
animal magnetism,

01:20:20.560 --> 01:20:23.050 align:middle line:84%
or Mesmerism as it
is sometimes called--

01:20:23.050 --> 01:20:27.610 align:middle line:84%
form a sort of backbone
to all later esotericism.

01:20:27.610 --> 01:20:32.040 align:middle line:84%
>> I went to all the different
four corners of the world.

01:20:32.040 --> 01:20:33.820 align:middle line:90%
It's all the same.

01:20:33.820 --> 01:20:38.110 align:middle line:84%
But it comes together
in one awareness.

01:20:38.110 --> 01:20:40.320 align:middle line:84%
The East, the West, the
North and the South.

01:20:40.320 --> 01:20:46.700 align:middle line:84%
They will meet in a new
consensus of questions.

01:20:46.700 --> 01:20:49.630 align:middle line:90%
Where do I come from?

01:20:49.630 --> 01:20:52.380 align:middle line:90%
Why am I here?

01:20:52.380 --> 01:20:56.070 align:middle line:90%
And what is the destiny of life?

01:20:56.070 --> 01:20:59.760 align:middle line:84%
>> In the 19th century
we have Spiritualism,

01:20:59.760 --> 01:21:01.860 align:middle line:90%
which really begins in America.

01:21:01.860 --> 01:21:05.300 align:middle line:84%
The classical date that is
mentioned for the beginnings

01:21:05.300 --> 01:21:07.770 align:middle line:90%
of this movement is 1848.

01:21:07.770 --> 01:21:12.420 align:middle line:84%
The very basic idea that it is
possible to have communication

01:21:12.420 --> 01:21:13.730 align:middle line:90%
with the spirits of the dead.

01:21:13.730 --> 01:21:16.500 align:middle line:84%
So that it is possible
to talk to them,

01:21:16.500 --> 01:21:20.130 align:middle line:84%
to receive messages
from them, and therefore

01:21:20.130 --> 01:21:24.210 align:middle line:84%
to know about what is going
to happen to us when we die.

01:21:24.210 --> 01:21:26.790 align:middle line:84%
Most of the messages
that are being received

01:21:26.790 --> 01:21:31.200 align:middle line:84%
through Spiritualism are in fact
related to the destiny of man

01:21:31.200 --> 01:21:32.060 align:middle line:90%
after death.

01:21:32.060 --> 01:21:37.150 align:middle line:84%
>> The soul is the property
of the microcosmos.

01:21:37.150 --> 01:21:46.512 align:middle line:84%
The human presence is,
I would say, a traveler

01:21:46.512 --> 01:21:48.350 align:middle line:90%
in time and space.

01:21:48.350 --> 01:21:53.220 align:middle line:84%
So I can't tell
you how many times

01:21:53.220 --> 01:21:58.500 align:middle line:90%
I came here again and again.

01:21:58.500 --> 01:22:00.710 align:middle line:90%
The transmigration of souls.

01:22:00.710 --> 01:22:03.400 align:middle line:10%
I would give myself
as an example.

01:22:03.400 --> 01:22:08.898 align:middle line:84%
My soul comes back at the
moment that I'm here again.

01:22:08.898 --> 01:22:11.378 align:middle line:90%
[PIANO MUSIC]

01:22:11.378 --> 01:22:18.830 align:middle line:90%


01:22:18.830 --> 01:22:22.240 align:middle line:84%
>> We tried to collect the
first editions of, for instance,

01:22:22.240 --> 01:22:24.606 align:middle line:90%
Madame Blavatsky's works.

01:22:24.606 --> 01:22:27.101 align:middle line:90%
[PIANO MUSIC]

01:22:27.101 --> 01:22:40.100 align:middle line:90%


01:22:40.100 --> 01:22:42.880 align:middle line:84%
>> Spiritualism is not
very much based on the idea

01:22:42.880 --> 01:22:43.860 align:middle line:90%
of a tradition.

01:22:43.860 --> 01:22:47.070 align:middle line:84%
It's more based on the
idea of direct experience.

01:22:47.070 --> 01:22:50.700 align:middle line:84%
You get together with a
group of sympathetic persons.

01:22:50.700 --> 01:22:54.990 align:middle line:84%
And then you engage in what
is usually called a seance.

01:22:54.990 --> 01:22:56.250 align:middle line:90%
With the help of a medium--

01:22:56.250 --> 01:22:58.950 align:middle line:84%
so, a person with the
particular skills--

01:22:58.950 --> 01:23:02.570 align:middle line:84%
you enter in contact with
the spirits of dead people.

01:23:02.570 --> 01:23:03.540 align:middle line:90%
It is that simple.

01:23:03.540 --> 01:23:06.487 align:middle line:84%
So you don't need to have a
particular tradition for that.

01:23:06.487 --> 01:23:08.982 align:middle line:90%
[PIANO MUSIC]

01:23:08.982 --> 01:23:35.980 align:middle line:90%


01:23:35.980 --> 01:23:39.420 align:middle line:84%
Occultism really begins around
